   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1814-09_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <note>
                  Written by <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
                  Signed by <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">R.L. Edgeworth</persName>
               </note>
               <dateline>
                  <name type="place" ref="Id_where"/>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworths Town</placeName>
                  <add>
                     <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#IE">Ireland</placeName>
                  </add>
                  <date when="1814-09-01">
                  <choice>
                     <orig>
                        <hi rend="superscript">tr</hi>
                     </orig>
                     <reg>September</reg>
                  </choice>. 1<hi rend="superscript">st</hi>. 1814</date></dateline>
               <salute>
                  <persName>My Dear Sir</persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I will not take up your time by <choice>
                  <orig>apolo<lb/>
               =gies</orig>
                  <reg>apologies</reg>
               </choice> - The object of this letter will I hope<lb/>
               be my excuse. A young gentleman<lb/>
               who has had an undue quantity of<lb/>
               latin &amp; greek early hammered into<lb/>
               his mind wants to be placed at some<lb/>
               school or with some tutor in the<lb/>
               neighborhood of <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Liverpool_ENK">Liverpool</placeName> where he<lb/>
               can learn other parts of knowledge<lb/>
               which are fully as necessary for the<lb/>
               business of life as classic lore. I have<lb/>
               been desired by a respectable friend<lb/>
               who has a high esteem for your <choice>
                  <orig>charac<lb/>
               =ter</orig>
                  <reg>character</reg>
               </choice> and attainments to request your<lb/>
               advice upon this important subject.<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2">Mrs.</persName> &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Miss Edgeworth</persName> send their <choice>
                  <orig>res-<lb/>
               pects</orig>
                  <reg>respects</reg>
               </choice> to you &amp; their compliments &amp;<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1814-09_page02.jpg"/>
               to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#RoscX1">Mrs. Roscoe</persName> and to your amiable<lb/>
               family - They remember with grateful<lb/>
               pleasure the happy day they passed at<lb/>
               your house<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               I am my dear Sir<lb/>
               with much esteem<lb/>
               Your <choice>
                  <orig>obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>.</orig>
                  <reg>obedient</reg>
               </choice> Servant,<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">
                  <choice>
                     <orig>Rich<hi rend="superscript">rd</hi>
                     </orig>
                     <reg>Richard</reg>
                  </choice> Lovell Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p>please to address your letter under<lb/>
                  cover to the <persName ref="./Personography.xml#FostJ2">
                     <choice>
                        <orig>R<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>.</orig>
                        <reg>Right</reg>
                     </choice>
                     <choice>
                        <orig>Hon<hi rend="superscript">ble</hi>.</orig>
                        <reg>Honorable</reg>
                     </choice> John Foster</persName>
                  <lb/>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Collon_IE">Collon Ireland</placeName>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </postscript>
         </div>
